          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Taxpayer Receipt Act</strong> </p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to require the Department of the Treasury to provide every taxpayer who files an individual income tax return for any taxable year an itemized tax receipt showing: (1) the proportionate allocation of the taxpayer's payment in such year among major expenditure categories of the federal budget (e.g., social security, national defense, Medicare and other federal health programs, low-income assistance programs, unemployment benefits, net interest on the federal debt, and other federal programs); and (2) the amount of the federal debt at the end of the fiscal year and the amount of additional borrowing by the federal government in such fiscal year for each legal U.S. resident.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-10-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
